is the desires of her man.

274
00:21:35,845 --> 00:21:38,671
How does it feel to be a bit more gentle?

275
00:21:38,671 --> 00:21:39,866
I didn't do that.

276
00:21:40,997 --> 00:21:44,144
We haven't got to the "dating stage" yet.

277
00:21:44,144 --> 00:21:47,557
But then Tsukasa, you spent a night alone with her.

278
00:21:49,664 --> 00:21:56,121
Ah. It's always best to be natural on the first.

279
00:21:59,305 --> 00:22:01,680
I can't let this go on...

280
00:22:01,680 --> 00:22:02,447
You've been together for a night...

281
00:22:02,447 --> 00:22:03,732
No way...

282
00:22:04,506 --> 00:22:06,484
I must be responsible for my actions.

283
00:22:06,484 --> 00:22:07,974
What "responsible"?

284
00:22:07,974 --> 00:22:12,707
Oh, yea... yea yea...

285
00:22:17,585 --> 00:22:19,085
Is Tsukasa alright?

286
00:22:19,647 --> 00:22:22,053
What's he going to do next?

287
00:22:26,664 --> 00:22:29,479
Next time, let's have a double date.

288
00:22:29,479 --> 00:22:31,799
I've said many times,

289
00:22:31,799 --> 00:22:35,394
that sort of thing (dating) never happened to us.

290
00:22:35,394 --> 00:22:39,092
You even said "us", that's admitting it.

291
00:22:39,092 --> 00:22:42,198
No way, I'm not saying anything else.

292
00:22:43,426 --> 00:22:46,148
Have mercy on me...

293
00:22:47,075 --> 00:22:50,442
You're so carefree, how I envy you, Yuuki.

294
00:22:50,442 --> 00:22:53,397
You get to study with people of similar tastes.

295
00:22:54,052 --> 00:22:58,276
You still can't forget that "Marble Eyes"?

296
00:22:58,276 --> 00:22:59,007
Eh?

297
00:22:59,007 --> 00:23:02,615
Makino, I really like your determination.

298
00:23:04,549 --> 00:23:06,413
Don't forget him.

299
00:23:06,413 --> 00:23:07,521
Lady boss.

300
00:23:07,521 --> 00:23:10,584
If you forget about a man,
another new one will appear.

301
00:23:10,584 --> 00:23:15,191
There will be new hurts,
new wounds of the heart.

302
00:23:15,191 --> 00:23:15,972
Oh.

303
00:23:15,972 --> 00:23:20,657
I used to love this man called John.

304
00:23:20,657 --> 00:23:21,859
He sounds like a foreigner.

305
00:23:21,859 --> 00:23:26,444
I forgot everything when I
was in by his warm arms.

306
00:23:26,444 --> 00:23:31,538
John!!! His other name was Lenon.

307
00:23:31,538 --> 00:23:32,382
Eh?

308
00:23:32,382 --> 00:23:34,473
In other words, John Lenon?

309
00:23:34,473 --> 00:23:38,669
Rounded spectacles really looked good on him.

310
00:23:39,899 --> 00:23:42,752
He was such a gentleman.

311
00:23:42,752 --> 00:23:46,425
I was completely taken in...

312
00:23:46,425 --> 00:23:49,668
I only needed to hear his gentle voice calling out to me...
I would forget everything else.

313
00:23:50,909 --> 00:23:53,836
We had such a lovely time together

314
00:23:53,836 --> 00:23:57,515
Old lady, isn't your real name Ono Yoko?

315
00:23:57,515 --> 00:23:59,267
"Sengoku Sachiyo"
(Lit: A thousand generations of happiness)

316
00:23:59,267 --> 00:24:06,721
Sigh... An opportunity wasted...
He was trivial like a small worm.

317
00:24:07,894 --> 00:24:10,158
What a joke.

318
00:24:13,628 --> 00:24:15,951
How old exactly is Lady Boss?

319
00:24:19,844 --> 00:24:26,381
You can't be too fast. To be loved,
one has to first love.

320
00:24:30,822 --> 00:24:32,283
Yes...

321
00:24:35,196 --> 00:24:42,913
There will be new hurts,
new wounds of the heart...?

322
00:24:46,249 --> 00:24:48,940
Maybe he really likes Tsukushi-chan.

323
00:24:52,638 --> 00:24:53,907
No no no...

324
00:24:56,518 --> 00:24:59,365
This is really unbelievable!

325
00:25:06,117 --> 00:25:07,489
Why is it like this?

326
00:25:08,326 --> 00:25:11,977
Why are you here? And you need to take off
your shoes before you come in.

327
00:25:11,977 --> 00:25:12,847
Why?

328
00:25:12,847 --> 00:25:17,499
Alright alright. Doumyoji-san is here to apologise
about what happened last night.

329
00:25:18,338 --> 00:25:22,941
Why didn't you tell us earlier that
you were together with the wealthy Doumyoji-san?

330
00:25:22,941 --> 00:25:24,321
Eh? But...

331
00:25:24,321 --> 00:25:32,463
From today onwards, I hope that you'll take good care of
my daughter until the two of you are old.

332
00:25:32,463 --> 00:25:34,277
That's how I feel as well.

333
00:25:34,277 --> 00:25:35,838
Wa... Wait... What are you all doing?

334
00:25:35,838 --> 00:25:38,944
Onii-sama, do you need me to get you
a bottle of beer?

335
00:25:38,944 --> 00:25:40,939
Oh, if you don't mind otou-to (little brother).

336
00:25:41,362 --> 00:25:42,926
No problem at all!

337
00:25:44,046 --> 00:25:45,595
It's not good to drink beer!

338
00:25:45,595 --> 00:25:46,884
Why are you all so nice to him?

339
00:25:46,884 --> 00:25:49,269
We're all family, right?

340
00:25:52,198 --> 00:25:54,201
I have something to say to you,
come here.

341
00:25:54,201 --> 00:25:55,599
What?

342
00:25:55,599 --> 00:25:56,750
Hurry up.

343
00:25:59,455 --> 00:26:00,457
Ma'am.

344
00:26:00,848 --> 00:26:03,400
I'm having my meal now, please don't bother me.

345
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:04,469
I know, but...

346
00:26:04,469 --> 00:26:05,723
Is it urgent?

347
00:26:07,819 --> 00:26:12,016
The piece of puzzle that we left in Tsukasa-sama room...

348
00:26:16,263 --> 00:26:23,482
Is it because he ignored the puzzle,
that Tsukasa-sama has more and more conflicts with you?

349
00:26:25,627 --> 00:26:27,281
Perhaps...

350
00:26:30,883 --> 00:26:34,412
I've said what I shouldn't have, please forgive me.

351
00:26:37,184 --> 00:26:39,110
Nishida.
Yes.

352
00:26:39,976 --> 00:26:42,274
Please check on Tsukasa's activities.

353
00:26:44,311 --> 00:26:45,543
I understand.

354
00:26:56,904 --> 00:26:59,669
Why isn't there anyone here?

355
00:27:00,214 --> 00:27:02,426
I've got this place covered.

356
00:27:02,426 --> 00:27:04,383
Oh, I see.

357
00:27:06,119 --> 00:27:07,466
Eh?

358
00:27:09,986 --> 00:27:13,219
Didn't you say you had something to talk about?

359
00:27:13,219 --> 00:27:16,305
Is that why you had this whole place emptied out?

360
00:27:17,282 --> 00:27:23,834
But I'm really touched,
it's the first time I visited a commoner's house.

361
00:27:25,499 --> 00:27:33,239
The way my family sees the value of things
is completely different from yours.

362
00:27:33,239 --> 00:27:36,897
So please don't suddenly visit us.

363
00:27:40,951 --> 00:27:42,653
You seem a bit wet.

364
00:27:43,865 --> 00:27:46,716
Hey, are you listening?

365
00:27:46,716 --> 00:27:48,499
Isn't that Rui's?

366
00:27:50,031 --> 00:27:50,875
Eh?

367
00:27:50,875 --> 00:27:52,878
You haven't returned it to him?

368
00:27:54,361 --> 00:27:56,002
Yea...

369
00:27:58,323 --> 00:28:02,961
You... Do you like Rui?

370
00:28:03,366 --> 00:28:04,906
Eh?

371
00:28:04,906 --> 00:28:11,752
Even if Rui is going after Shizuka,
do you still secretly love him?

372
00:28:13,815 --> 00:28:16,278
It's not like that.

373
00:28:16,278 --> 00:28:18,521
Anyway, it's none of your business.

374
00:28:18,521 --> 00:28:20,107
Who says it's none of my business?

375
00:28:20,107 --> 00:28:21,311
Eh?

376
00:28:21,782 --> 00:28:27,492
Rui... He really likes apples.

377
00:28:27,492 --> 00:28:28,727
Huh?

378
00:28:29,409 --> 00:28:35,587
But he only eats shredded apples.

379
00:28:36,327 --> 00:28:42,497
But I believe that it's more manly to just
eat the apple bite by bite.

380
00:28:42,497 --> 00:28:43,951
Hey Rui!

381
00:28:44,854 --> 00:28:46,830
Can you stop that scratching sound?

382
00:28:46,830 --> 00:28:48,465
If you continue scratching, you'll become a Buddha.
(Another of Tsukasa's bad jokes.
The word to describe the scratching sound in Japanese
is likened to a Buddha.)

383
00:28:48,465 --> 00:28:51,631
Don't worry. I'm Christian.

384
00:28:52,381 --> 00:28:54,210
Tsukasa.

385
00:28:54,210 --> 00:28:56,166
There's still a lot of apple tea left.

386
00:28:56,166 --> 00:29:00,414
Soujiro, can you stop being so obsessed with tea?
Talk about something more cool.

387
00:29:00,414 --> 00:29:02,641
That's not bad too, Tsukasa.

388
00:29:02,641 --> 00:29:05,320
Hey Soujiro, want to try some dance moves?

389
00:29:05,320 --> 00:29:08,752
I must say first that it has nothing to do with me.

390
00:29:11,238 --> 00:29:15,796
That was the first time they just ignored
what I said.

391
00:29:19,973 --> 00:29:23,097
Hey, you guys, look here.
This is how you eat an apple

392
00:29:23,097 --> 00:29:26,370
It's much more convenient than making it
into powder.

393
00:29:28,923 --> 00:29:33,911
As for me, I never learnt to eat like that.

394
00:29:33,911 --> 00:29:35,169
Hang on a sec.

395
00:29:35,648 --> 00:29:37,886
Hanazawa Rui really said that?

396
00:29:37,886 --> 00:29:40,104
He said something like that.

397
00:29:40,104 --> 00:29:41,718
In other words, you made it up (fiction).

398
00:29:41,718 --> 00:29:47,978
Still, Rui eats apples like that.

399
00:29:47,978 --> 00:29:52,044
And I was extremely annoyed by the way he ate it.

400
00:30:00,442 --> 00:30:09,092
Rui, if you continue eating apples,
it's more easy for you to become bald.

401
00:30:09,092 --> 00:30:10,224
Eh?

402
00:30:11,808 --> 00:30:18,144
From then onwards, he never ate another apple
that he once loved.

403
00:30:20,444 --> 00:30:25,657
I took away what Rui loved the most.

404
00:30:27,446 --> 00:30:29,654
That was during early spring last year.

405
00:30:31,501 --> 00:30:32,541
Umm...

406
00:30:32,541 --> 00:30:41,613
But, I never thought I would say those things about
becoming bald and all.

407
00:30:43,459 --> 00:30:47,959
Although I don't really know what you're talking about...

408
00:30:47,959 --> 00:30:49,506
It is like that.

409
00:30:49,506 --> 00:30:52,570
That's just what happened between Rui and I.

410
00:30:52,570 --> 00:30:53,342
Truthfully?

411
00:30:53,342 --> 00:30:54,462
It was just like that.

412
00:30:54,462 --> 00:30:55,372
Oh!

413
00:30:55,372 --> 00:30:56,611
Rui!

414
00:30:56,611 --> 00:30:58,833
That was why at the airport...

415
00:30:59,654 --> 00:31:01,395
I still don't get it.

416
00:31:03,114 --> 00:31:09,208
That's why I say you still love Rui.

417
00:31:09,195 --> 00:31:10,102
I...

418
00:31:10,102 --> 00:31:11,365
Umm...

419
00:31:11,365 --> 00:31:16,625
What if... What if I actually liked Rui?

420
00:31:17,172 --> 00:31:19,713
He's still got Shizuka-san.

421
00:31:23,318 --> 00:31:28,958
If you really like him, he'll definitely fall for you as well.

422
00:31:28,977 --> 00:31:30,610
Eh?

423
00:31:32,282 --> 00:31:38,750
I've seen many women, and they've always done it.

424
00:31:59,699 --> 00:32:01,096
You're back!

425
00:32:03,329 --> 00:32:04,860
Good work! Tsukushi.

426
00:32:04,860 --> 00:32:06,825
You must become a modern lady, Tsukushi.

427
00:32:06,825 --> 00:32:08,800
It's no longer a dream that we can all be rich and famous.

428
00:32:08,800 --> 00:32:10,199
I'm going to buy lots of beer!

429
00:32:10,199 --> 00:32:12,453
In the future when I have lots of money,
I'll buy many games.

430
00:32:12,453 --> 00:32:13,713
Buy buy buy...

431
00:32:18,612 --> 00:32:19,880
Umm...

432
00:32:21,319 --> 00:32:23,050
I've thought about it.

433
00:32:23,050 --> 00:32:24,249
How?

434
00:32:24,594 --> 00:32:29,167
That guy really is an idiot.

435
00:32:29,186 --> 00:32:30,382
Eh?

436
00:32:34,205 --> 00:32:37,690
He's serious about it, Tsukushi.

437
00:32:38,344 --> 00:32:40,552
It can't be.

438
00:32:47,671 --> 00:32:50,460
Why hasn't Sakurako come back to school?

439
00:32:50,460 --> 00:32:53,750
Hey, Tsuki. Don't forget about our outing later today.

440
00:32:53,761 --> 00:32:54,454
Eh?

441
00:32:54,454 --> 00:32:57,369
Didn't agree that we'll go to the Club and have lots of fun?

442
00:32:57,369 --> 00:32:59,049
C... Club?

443
00:32:59,688 --> 00:33:02,653
I'm sorry, I was forced to go.

444
00:33:02,653 --> 00:33:06,042
I got it. I'll let the Lady Boss know.

445
00:33:06,678 --> 00:33:08,850
Oh, we've got customers, bye.

446
00:33:08,850 --> 00:33:09,918
Welcome.

447
00:33:09,918 --> 00:33:11,804
Is Makino Tsukushi around?

448
00:33:13,442 --> 00:33:16,013
I'm sorry, she didn't come for work today.

449
00:33:16,013 --> 00:33:18,096
Are you on good terms with Makino?

450
00:33:18,096 --> 00:33:20,573
Well, we've been friends since middle school (secondary school).

451
00:33:20,573 --> 00:33:22,815
Well, then you should be Makino's good friend.

452
00:33:22,815 --> 00:33:23,761
I guess...

453
00:33:24,113 --> 00:33:27,083
You got some time to spare? We'd like to take you with us.

454
00:33:28,972 --> 00:33:31,115
Umm... I have work now...

455
00:33:31,115 --> 00:33:32,460
It's okay...

456
00:33:32,460 --> 00:33:34,294
Wait... Lady Boss!

457
00:33:34,294 --> 00:33:36,526
Wait a minute, what are you trying to do?

458
00:33:36,526 --> 00:33:38,173
We'd like to borrow this girl for a while.

459
00:33:38,173 --> 00:33:40,902
What's this all about? I'm calling the police.

460
00:33:40,902 --> 00:33:43,708
Everything... I'll buy it all.

461
00:33:47,081 --> 00:33:48,284
This whole place.

462
00:33:48,284 --> 00:33:49,304
Have fun.

463
00:33:49,304 --> 00:33:50,697
You can change so fast.

464
00:33:50,697 --> 00:33:52,307
Do you accept payment by card?

465
00:33:52,307 --> 00:33:54,489
Hey wait! Lady Boss!

466
00:33:55,422 --> 00:33:56,779
So similar...

467
00:33:57,769 --> 00:34:00,841
To a man I've met before.

468
00:34:12,376 --> 00:34:14,120
They're good...

469
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:15,986
You can do that later, have a drink first.

470
00:34:16,853 --> 00:34:19,091
Cheers!

471
00:34:21,187 --> 00:34:24,750
Hey hey. Don't you think that guy is great?

472
00:34:24,737 --> 00:34:28,083
No way, he's soooo handsome.

473
00:34:28,587 --> 00:34:31,595
Don't you think, he looks a bit like Hanazawa Rui?

474
00:34:31,595 --> 00:34:33,457
Eh? There is a resemblance.

475
00:34:33,457 --> 00:34:34,895
He's looking here!

476
00:34:34,895 --> 00:34:36,404
No way, he's coming.

477
00:34:36,404 --> 00:34:38,019
He's here already.

478
00:34:39,092 --> 00:34:41,705
- Hi there.
- Hi.

479
00:34:41,705 --> 00:34:44,275
I'm going to the washroom.

480
00:34:45,629 --> 00:34:47,876
Are you alone?

481
00:34:47,876 --> 00:34:50,750
Hey, do you want to join me down here?

482
00:34:50,770 --> 00:34:54,586
He really does look like Rui.

483
00:35:05,475 --> 00:35:08,278
Tsukasa has fallen into the river of love
and he doesn't care about the consequences at all.

484
00:35:08,800 --> 00:35:12,708
Although I feel that it's OK for
Tsukasa and Makino to be toghether.

485
00:35:14,664 --> 00:35:18,241
But I don't want Tsukasa to fall too deep into this.

486
00:35:18,628 --> 00:35:21,345
That's between the two of them.

487
00:35:24,087 --> 00:35:27,001
I don't think we should interfere.

488
00:35:28,016 --> 00:35:30,066
It's okay if they're just playing.

489
00:35:30,066 --> 00:35:33,375
But what if both of them run into serious problems.

490
00:35:33,385 --> 00:35:34,637
You get it?

491
00:35:35,798 --> 00:35:37,307
I don't get it.

492
00:35:37,307 --> 00:35:39,091
You don't understand?

493
00:35:40,317 --> 00:35:43,552
I don't understand what both of you
are trying to get at.

494
00:35:44,319 --> 00:35:45,884
I'll take my leave now.

495
00:35:46,219 --> 00:35:47,488
Ah, wait.

496
00:35:47,488 --> 00:35:49,111
Don't bother about her.

497
00:35:50,570 --> 00:35:53,216
She's the type that gives me a big headache.

498
00:36:10,579 --> 00:36:12,377
Sakurako?

499
00:36:14,596 --> 00:36:15,747
How can it be?

500
00:36:16,970 --> 00:36:18,127
Hey hey.

501
00:36:19,635 --> 00:36:20,305
Here.

502
00:36:20,305 --> 00:36:21,053
Eh?

503
00:36:21,053 --> 00:36:22,041
For you.

504
00:36:24,090 --> 00:36:25,670
Is that beer (sake)?

505
00:36:25,670 --> 00:36:28,742
No, it's not. It's oolong tea.

506
00:36:29,620 --> 00:36:31,235
If you don't mind.

507
00:36:31,235 --> 00:36:32,064
Cheers.

508
00:36:40,569 --> 00:36:42,608
What's your name?

509
00:36:43,270 --> 00:36:46,982
I'm Makino Tsukushi.

510
00:36:46,982 --> 00:36:50,917
Tsukushi-chan? That's a cute.

511
00:36:50,925 --> 00:36:52,508
Oh... No...

512
00:36:54,794 --> 00:36:58,750
Hey, why don't you follow me out?

513
00:36:58,754 --> 00:37:01,138
Eh?

514
00:37:01,138 --> 00:37:02,587
But...

515
00:37:02,587 --> 00:37:05,083
It's nothing much... Let's go.

516
00:37:40,117 --> 00:37:41,509
A dream?

517
00:37:47,261 --> 00:37:48,284
Eh?

518
00:38:02,964 --> 00:38:04,207
It's not a dream.

519
00:38:04,207 --> 00:38:06,875
Why am I like this? Don't tell me that guy...

520
00:38:07,401 --> 00:38:13,250
Oh no! What have I been doing?

521
00:38:17,099 --> 00:38:19,583
I didn't do anything. Nothing at all.

522
00:38:19,576 --> 00:38:22,816
And the first time always involves some bleeding...
(Hint hint)

523
00:38:22,816 --> 00:38:23,485
HEY!

524
00:38:23,485 --> 00:38:24,607
Woah!

525
00:38:26,593 --> 00:38:29,208
It's already noon. What have you been doing?

526
00:38:29,549 --> 00:38:31,939
Have you been waiting long for me?

527
00:38:33,066 --> 00:38:34,427
Who says I'm waiting for you?

528
00:38:35,109 --> 00:38:37,245
I just happened to be passing by.

529
00:38:37,758 --> 00:38:39,961
But then you'd be going in the opposite direction

530
00:38:39,961 --> 00:38:41,088
You talk too much!

531
00:38:42,618 --> 00:38:43,866
Get in!

532
00:38:53,554 --> 00:38:55,958
Having lunch with F4? How envious.

533
00:38:55,971 --> 00:38:58,958
We can't forgive her. Definitely not.

534
00:38:58,942 --> 00:39:00,377
Yuriko.

535
00:39:11,663 --> 00:39:14,356
What would you like to eat?

536
00:39:14,356 --> 00:39:15,533
It's okay.

537
00:39:16,218 --> 00:39:18,379
You don't normally get to eat good food.

538
00:39:18,379 --> 00:39:19,807
So don't worry.

539
00:39:20,272 --> 00:39:21,618
But, I've got my own packed lunch.

540
00:39:21,618 --> 00:39:22,574
Really, there's no need.

541
00:39:22,574 --> 00:39:24,824
Don't make us men lose our dignity!

542
00:39:25,711 --> 00:39:27,207
Where did you go yesterday?

543
00:39:28,002 --> 00:39:29,819
We were looking for you at your working place,

544
00:39:29,819 --> 00:39:31,472
but the told us you took the day off.

545
00:39:31,472 --> 00:39:34,173
Ah... You went there...

546
00:39:34,173 --> 00:39:36,217
I had something on yesterday...

547
00:39:36,217 --> 00:39:38,023
Maybe it's another man.

548
00:39:38,733 --> 00:39:40,912
Hey hey hey... Is that true?

549
00:39:40,912 --> 00:39:43,482
She doesn't look like the type to do those sort of things.

550
00:39:43,482 --> 00:39:44,709
I...

551
00:39:45,459 --> 00:39:47,663
Makino is certainly not that type of girl!!

552
00:39:47,663 --> 00:39:51,212
Even for you guys,
you will talk when your sleep.

553
00:39:51,212 --> 00:39:53,728
But when you're awake and talking,
you don't call that talking in your sleep

554
00:39:53,728 --> 00:39:57,140
You might say what you say in your sleep when you are awake,

555
00:39:57,140 --> 00:40:01,182
but when you're awake, you don't say
what you won't say when you're asleep.

556
00:40:01,182 --> 00:40:04,557
What you say when you're awake,
you say it because you're not asleep...

557
00:40:04,557 --> 00:40:06,243
What the heck are you saying?

558
00:40:06,243 --> 00:40:07,864
You yourself don't even know what you're talking about.

559
00:40:07,864 --> 00:40:08,978
Shut up!

560
00:40:08,978 --> 00:40:12,250
In other words, you should say what you would say
in your sleep, when you sleep.

561
00:40:13,540 --> 00:40:15,827
I think he meant REM sleep.
(REM - Rapid Eye Movement. A sleeping disorder.)

562
00:40:15,827 --> 00:40:16,904
He sleeps like a ram.

563
00:40:16,904 --> 00:40:18,253
Why are we talking about goat meat?

564
00:40:18,253 --> 00:40:20,383
Yes!

565
00:40:25,522 --> 00:40:27,083
That guy is easily excited.

566
00:40:38,026 --> 00:40:39,369
Sakurako?

567
00:40:43,160 --> 00:40:44,437
Eh?

568
00:40:48,374 --> 00:40:52,265
It's best if it doesn't get worse than this.

569
00:40:52,836 --> 00:40:59,167
Tsukushi, nothing really happened that night?

570
00:40:59,181 --> 00:41:00,366
No no no no...

571
00:41:00,366 --> 00:41:02,100
Definitely not.

572
00:41:03,041 --> 00:41:06,372
You better be serious about what
doing you and Doumyoji-san are doing.

573
00:41:06,819 --> 00:41:08,697
What? Why arey you suddenly saying this?

574
00:41:09,830 --> 00:41:11,833
If you can't take it,

575
00:41:11,833 --> 00:41:14,628
or if you don't like it then just tell him straight.

576
00:41:17,245 --> 00:41:20,236
But, it doesn't make a difference whether
I reject him or not.

577
00:41:20,236 --> 00:41:23,769
Anyway, I don't think he truly likes me.

578
00:41:23,769 --> 00:41:25,051
He does like you.

579
00:41:27,072 --> 00:41:31,879
And Doumyoji's friends are truly worried about
the two of you.

580
00:41:31,879 --> 00:41:33,085
But then, Yuuki,

581
00:41:33,085 --> 00:41:36,268
the two of them are still rich kids.

582
00:41:36,268 --> 00:41:37,915
You'd better be careful.

583
00:41:37,915 --> 00:41:40,886
I don't know what those two are really like,

584
00:41:40,886 --> 00:41:43,619
but I can tell they're sincere from what they said.

585
00:41:45,208 --> 00:41:48,929
Doumyoji-san is actually a very lonely person.

586
00:41:52,420 --> 00:41:55,806
I heard he was brought up by a mother who
is constantly unhappy about things around her.

587
00:42:06,832 --> 00:42:09,063
He lived in a very harsh environment.

588
00:42:09,063 --> 00:42:11,959
Perhaps that's why he's overbearing.

589
00:42:13,980 --> 00:42:16,614
Actually, beyond his fierce front,

590
00:42:16,614 --> 00:42:20,660
he yearns to be loved by someone.

591
00:42:25,672 --> 00:42:28,302
"Yearns to be loved"...

592
00:42:36,823 --> 00:42:39,658
Some outrageous things have been done to me.

593
00:42:42,849 --> 00:42:45,491
I really don't get it.

594
00:42:57,315 --> 00:42:58,716
Good morning.

595
00:43:04,171 --> 00:43:05,902
Hey... What's wrong?

596
00:43:10,421 --> 00:43:12,721
Don't act dumb, you...

597
00:43:12,721 --> 00:43:15,888
You took advantage of the trust Doumyoji-san had in you.

598
00:43:15,888 --> 00:43:18,500
I still can't believe you actually did such a thing.

599
00:43:18,486 --> 00:43:20,503
What are you saying?

600
00:43:22,134 --> 00:43:24,306
Don't spout nonsense.

601
00:43:24,674 --> 00:43:27,792
Come here! Tsuki...

602
00:43:28,478 --> 00:43:31,875
It hurts! What are you doing?!

603
00:43:34,384 --> 00:43:35,468
Take a look!

604
00:43:37,076 --> 00:43:39,458
Stop it! Let me go!

605
00:43:48,106 --> 00:43:49,413
Take a good look.

606
00:43:52,632 --> 00:43:54,906
<Please enjoy freely>

607
00:44:10,609 --> 00:44:11,798
What's that?

608
00:44:11,798 --> 00:44:16,051
What you've done is the most demeaning thing
a woman can ever do.

609
00:44:16,051 --> 00:44:17,429
No! This...

610
00:44:17,429 --> 00:44:19,129
Still denying it?

611
00:44:20,364 --> 00:44:22,265
Not only was it Doumyoji-san,

612
00:44:22,714 --> 00:44:27,132
you deceived everyone in Eitoku Gakuen.

613
00:44:27,132 --> 00:44:30,186
Even if you rely on all your previous methods,
we won't give in to you.

614
00:44:30,952 --> 00:44:33,618
I suggest you prepare yourself!

615
00:44:34,331 --> 00:44:35,890
What are you doing!!

616
00:44:40,906 --> 00:44:42,422
What do you think you're doing...?

617
00:44:42,422 --> 00:44:44,159
Please take a look at this.

618
00:44:51,431 --> 00:44:53,128
It's not what you think, Doumyoji.

619
00:45:02,171 --> 00:45:03,641
What's the meaning of this, Makino?

620
00:45:03,641 --> 00:45:08,333
I think I was taken advantage of
by someone who really hates me.

621
00:45:17,640 --> 00:45:19,082
Believe me...

622
00:46:18,375 --> 00:46:19,917
I must definitely find out who did this.

623
00:46:19,960 --> 00:46:22,874
Love. It happens when you least expect it.

624
00:46:22,917 --> 00:46:24,583
That woman is highly dangerous.

625
00:46:24,626 --> 00:46:27,292
I can't let him go.

626
00:46:27,333 --> 00:46:29,170
I will kill you.

